<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Troutdale Digital Heritage Guide</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@700&family=Source+Sans+Pro:wght@400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --ths-blue: #003366; /* Deep Historical Blue */
            --ths-gold: #c5a059; /* Heritage Gold */
            --ths-cream: #f9f7f2; /* Parchment White */
            --ths-text: #333333;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--ths-cream);
            color: var(--ths-text);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: var(--ths-blue);
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 4px solid var(--ths-gold);
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        h1, h2 { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; margin: 0; }
        
        .live-broadcast-btn {
            background: #d9534f;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 25px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 10px;
            display: inline-block;
            text-decoration: none;
            animation: pulse 2s infinite;
        }

        @keyframes pulse {
            0% { transform: scale(1); }
            50% { transform: scale(1.05); }
            100% { transform: scale(1); }
        }

        .container { padding: 15px; max-width: 600px; margin: auto; }

        .tour-section { margin-bottom: 40px; }
        
        .tour-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border-left: 5px solid var(--ths-blue);
        }

        .image-placeholder {
            background: #ddd;
            height: 200px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-style: italic;
            color: #777;
        }

        .content { padding: 20px; }

        .audio-player {
            background: #f1f1f1;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: space-between;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }

        button.play-btn {
            background: var(--ths-blue);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 8px 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .footer { text-align: center; font-size: 0.8em; padding: 20px; color: #777; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Troutdale Heritage</h1>
    <p>Official Walking Companion</p>
    <a href="#" class="live-broadcast-btn">🔴 JOIN LIVE GUIDE AUDIO</a>
</header>

<div class="container">

    <div class="tour-section">
        <h2>The Gateway Tour</h2>
        <p>Starting at the Centennial Arch</p>

        <div class="tour-card">
            <div class="image-placeholder">Photo: The Centennial Arch</div>
            <div class="content">
                <h3>Stop 1: The Centennial Arch</h3>
                <p>Dedicated in 2007, this arch marks the entrance to the Historic Columbia River Highway. It represents Troutdale's legacy as the 'Gateway to the Gorge.'</p>
                <div class="audio-player">
                    <span>Listen to History</span>
                    <button class="play-btn">▶ Play Audio</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tour-card">
            <div class="image-placeholder">Photo: Rail Depot Museum</div>
            <div class="content">
                <h3>Stop 2: The Depot Rail Museum</h3>
                <p>The railroad was the lifeblood of Troutdale. This 1907 depot served passengers and freight for decades before becoming a museum.</p>
                <div class="audio-player">
                    <span>Listen to History</span>
                    <button class="play-btn">▶ Play Audio</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr style="border: 1px solid var(--ths-gold); margin: 40px 0;">

    <div class="tour-section">
        <h2>Ch'ak Ch'ak Trail</h2>
        <p>Sharon Nesbit Heritage Park</p>

        <div class="tour-card">
            <div class="image-placeholder">Photo: Sandy River Trestle</div>
            <div class="content">
                <h3>Stop 1: The UP Trestle</h3>
                <p>Named 'Ch'ak Ch'ak' (Bald Eagle) in Chinuk Wawa, this trail passes under the massive Union Pacific trestle, a feat of early engineering.</p>
                <div class="audio-player">
                    <span>Listen to History</span>
                    <button class="play-btn">▶ Play Audio</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tour-card">
            <div class="image-placeholder">Photo: Sharon Nesbit Heritage Park</div>
            <div class="content">
                <h3>Stop 2: Heritage Park</h3>
                <p>Dedicated to local historian Sharon Nesbit, this park connects the city to the Sandy River. Keep an eye out for ospreys and eagles!</p>
                <div class="audio-player">
                    <span>Listen to History</span>
                    <button class="play-btn">▶ Play Audio</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="footer">
    &copy; 2026 Troutdale Historical Society<br>
    Preserving the past for our future.
</div>

</body>
</html>
